  "title": "wt merge: data safety, rebase, and worktree cleanup",
  "summary": "The `wt merge` command lands a feature branch onto the target, runs the rebase, performs cleanup of the merged worktree, and runs pre-/post-merge hooks. Critical data-safety surface: a failed merge must not silently discard uncommitted work, and cleanup must not run before approval. See CLAUDE.md > Data Safety and Project Commands Run Only After Approval.",
